1. USE iso646.h style operator keywords:
2. try to make line length no more that 80 characters
3. if a declaration or definition of a function is too long, try to put
    arguments in next line first to fit the rule above, or else if the arguments
    list is too long, then align them in vertical.
4. Use astyle to format codes, with a modified style ANSI:
    --style=ansi --indent=spaces=4 --indent-preprocessor --indent-switches
    --indent-cases --brackets=break --pad-paren-out --pad-header --unpad-paren
    --break-closing-brackets --align-pointer=name --min-conditional-indent=4
    --max-instatement-indent=50 --lineend=linux --indent-labels